= Vector Intersect =
#context: sop
#type: node

"""Finds intersection points between line vectors in the input geometry."""

== Overview ==

Vector Intersect computes the intersection (or closest point) between pairs of line vectors defined in the input geometry and outputs the resulting intersection points.

@parameters

Tolerance:
    #id: tolerance
    Maximum distance between two lines to be considered intersecting. Pairs farther apart than this threshold are ignored.
